What is CI CD ??

Continuous integration and continuous deployment

We build a pipeline

We build the code

Deploy the code
We automate it

We use plugins for integration

Automatically deploy enhancements 


What is SDLC ??
Software Development Lifecycle

From the time the software is developed till it reaches the client / customer 

Building the packages - build steps

Archiving or packaging the complete code/program

For eg - 
Windows based applications are developed using .Net

I get a file called as .exe or .msi

Mostly packages are —
Java - jar
Nodejs - tar file with xml
.net - .exe or .msi


Monolithic vs micro service ??

Big code broken into pieces - 

Shell process - 

Su - ubuntu —> creates a shell (process id 101) 
 — run dd command in bg 102
 — run vi 
  — nodes app
 — run bash 104

Flipkart - jar (single jar)
 — homepage
 — categories
 — cart
 — payment
 — orders
 — login

Monolithic means —> in one single code base, it has all the features -> if something goes wrong, whole application will be down, in case of a patching or a new feature release, you have to build the complete package
Eg - for small organization with less customer base 
It is tightly coupled with each other 

Microservice 
It is not tightly coupled with each other , 
Flipkart  —>
 — homepage - war
 — categories - jar
 — cart - .net
 — payment - nodes
 — orders - python
 — login - jar


SDLC 

Feature or requirement or new enhancement
Architecture ,Code base will be decided
Code will be developed
Code is scanned (integrity, syntax errors, code quality checks, etc)
Code is built
Tested
Deployed to the actual server from where the client can access
Monitor 


Waterfall 
Agile 

