Servers for applications, for database, for middleware , etc
—> staging / sandbox environment, (production grade replica / clone)
—> production environment	

SCm - source code management , Version control systems
GIT - command or package used
Eg - GitHub, gitlab, bitbucket, azure devops, etc
Main or master branch 

CircleCI, etc

Jenkins - automation tool

Once the code is build to a jar or war or .exe file or tar file, this is a build artifact 
Artifacts are not uploaded usually to the same repository, it will be uploaded to artifactory tools like jfrog, nexus, etc


GitHub —> aws codecommit
Jenkins pipeline —> aws code pipeline 
To build a package , Jenkins (maven) —> aws code build 
Artifacts - nexus, jfrog —> aww code artifacts


Azure - azure devops


Cloudwatch - 
It is used for monitoring all the aws resources , it has metrics, events , logs , alarms and dashboards.


Metrics - 
Eg - cpu, mem/RAM, storage, network in/out, disk IOPS, rate, latencies, etc


Events —>
Status, health checks, messages, reasons, ,etc - events

Logs - 
Detailed information about the system or raw information 

Alarms - 
Monitors
Sitting a threshold and triggering an alarm 
For eg - monitor the RAM/MEM usage , it should not go above 75 percent, for last 5 mins, periodically check

Native - cpu usage, disk usage, network usage, etc
Custom metrics - no of processes run by user ubuntu , command


1 physical serve in aws - 100 VMs (cpu will be dedicated)
For eg - second VM —> 1 core, 1 GB Memory, 
From the above, 1 core will be allocated from physical server, the 1 GB is elastic, 300 MB of utilization, only that much will be occupied from the physical server, 

What is SNS - 
Its a simple notification service
, concept - pub/sub
Publishing / subscribing 
Cloud watch will publish a value or a message to SNS
We will subscribe to sns topic like CPU alarm, we will receive the notification

Recipients - whom the notification should be sent - subscribers
Topic - cloud watch or other service can publish their message to a topic in SNS




Async - 
SNS - more of a FIFO
U send the message and forget it
Someone will subscribe and receive the message


SQS - Sync way
Simple queue service 

If u have micro services, from one service to another service it can send some messages and things to process 
For eg - in flipkart, the cart page can send for processing if order is placed to order service , 3 replicas, 
To manage the messaging, we use messaging queues, —> Producers and consumers

Eg - SQS , apache ActiveMQ,, Kafka 
Install and configure kafka, dev will tell who is the producer and consumer and they will configure it



Monitoring tools and alternatives - 
Cloud watch - only aws and aws related resources
Nagios, icinga, zabbix, prometheus

The above are for infra monitoring
For backend applications, you can monitor the thread usage , latency, requests coming to and from other apps, correlation, logs 
Application Performance Monitoring - APM 

For web application or browser based applications — Real user monitoring  (RUM) or synthetic monitoring

URL based monitoring - uptime monitoring

Logs - logs monitoring

Observability stack- all infra, APM, logs, synthetics etc monitoring under one tool for correlation 
Eg - New Relic, Datadog, Splunk, ELK, Dynatrace etc
Free ones - Elastic (ELK), prometheus Grafana

SRE- Create SLA, SLO/SLI , MTTR , etc








